excerpt: Local landmark wins fans with its seafood-driven Hawaiian menu, Polynesian decor & epic ocean views.
detail_description: Mama's Fish House, located on Maui's north shore, is a renowned local landmark offering a seafood-driven Hawaiian menu and stunning ocean views. The restaurant has received accolades such as being a semi-finalist for the 2018 James Beard Foundation Awards and ranking as the second most popular restaurant in the U.S. on OpenTable. With daily farm-to-table deliveries, their menus constantly change to showcase fresh, locally caught fish as the star of the show.
name: Mama's Fish House
address: 799 Poho Pl, Paia, HI 96779, USA

excerpt: Counter-serve cafe featuring farm-fresh American eats & handmade baked goods in a quaint setting.
detail_description: Leoda's Kitchen and Pie Shop is a charming counter-serve cafe located in Lahaina, offering farm-fresh American cuisine and delectable handmade baked goods. The restaurant boasts a cozy atmosphere inspired by Hawaiian plantations, where guests can indulge in a variety of savory and sweet dishes. From fresh tuna salad sandwiches to house-baked breads and locally sourced ingredients, the menu showcases an array of 'grandma comfort food' favorites.
name: Leoda's Kitchen and Pie Shop
address: 820 Olowalu Village Rd, Lahaina, HI 96761, USA

excerpt: Casual stop with a nautical theme & indoor picnic tables for seafood, plate lunches & fish burgers.
detail_description: Paia Fish Market Restaurant is a popular eatery located at the corner of Hana Hwy. and Baldwin Ave. It's known for its casual nautical theme and focus on delicious seafood, plate lunches, and fish burgers. The restaurant offers about 6 fresh fish varieties daily, prepared in various ways until they run out. Some favorites include blackened Ahi sashimi and Cajun-style Opah burger with wasabi butter and cheese fries.
name: Paia Fish Market Restaurant
address: 100 Hana Hwy, Paia, HI 96779, USA

excerpt: Farm-to-table eatery & bar for Hawaiian food, beer & cocktails, served in a casual space.
detail_description: Monkeypod Kitchen by Merriman in Wailea, Maui is a farm-to-table restaurant and bar that offers Hawaiian cuisine, beer, and cocktails in a laid-back setting. It's a hit with both tourists and locals, especially the Whalers Village location which is always bustling. The signature Monkeypod Mai Tai made with two types of rum, lime, macadamia nut orgeat, orange curacao, and honey-lilikoi foam is not to be missed.
name: Monkeypod Kitchen by Merriman - Wailea, Maui
address: 10 Wailea Gateway Pl B-201, Kihei, HI 96753, USA

excerpt: Renowned oceanfront restaurant features farm-to-table cuisine in an elegant setting with views.
detail_description: Merriman's Kapalua is a renowned oceanfront restaurant located at the point on Kapalua Bay in the Kapalua Resort. The restaurant features Hawaiian regional cuisine by James Beard award-winning Chef Peter Merriman, known for his farm-to-table commitment with over 90% of ingredients locally sourced. The elegant indoor dining area offers romantic ambiance with cozy, candlelit tables and vaulted ceilings. At sunset, diners can capture breathtaking views as the sun disappears over the ocean.
name: Merriman's Kapalua
address: 1 Bay Club Pl, Lahaina, HI 96761, USA

excerpt: Acclaimed destination for Hawaiian regional cuisine features a pineapple plantation-styled setting.
detail_description: Nestled on the picturesque slopes of Haleakala in Maui's Upcountry region, Hali'imaile General Store is a renowned culinary destination offering a modern twist on Hawaiian regional cuisine. Originally a plantation store dating back to 1925, it was transformed into a restaurant in 1988 by Chef Bev Gannon and has since gained international acclaim. The restaurant prides itself on its farm-to-table dining experience, featuring locally sourced ingredients in an idyllic Upcountry setting.
name: Hali'imaile General Store
address: 900 Haliimaile Rd, Haliimaile, HI 96768, USA

excerpt: Bustling local counter turning out pork belly bowls, garlic noodles & other Hawaiian comfort fare.
detail_description: Tin Roof Maui is a bustling local counter located near Maui's main airport, offering a convenient entry point for travelers seeking Hawaiian comfort food. Run by renowned chef Sheldon Simeon and his wife Janice, the restaurant serves up soulful dishes that reflect Simeon's Hilo roots. The menu features local specialties such as mochiko chicken, garlic shrimp, macaroni salad, saimin noodles, and chow fun noodles.
name: Tin Roof Maui
address: 360 Papa Pl Ste 116, Kahului, HI 96732, USA

excerpt: Asian shared plates, noodle dishes & sake cocktails in an airy, light, wood-trimmed space.
detail_description: Nestled in Lahaina, Hawaii, Star Noodle is a beloved spot known for its Asian shared plates, noodle dishes, and sake cocktails. Since 2010, this hotspot has been serving up traditional Hawaiian comfort food in a cool space with an ocean view. The menu features a variety of shareable starter plates like smashed cucumber salads with miso-chili sauce, steamed clams with miso butter, and adobo ribs with black pepper vinegar.
name: Star Noodle
address: 1287 Front St, Lahaina, HI 96761, USA

excerpt: Casual, modern pick for a sharable Filipino & Hawaiian family recipes plus a traveling dim-sum cart.
detail_description: Lineage is a casual and modern restaurant that offers a blend of Filipino and Hawaiian family recipes, along with a traveling dim-sum cart. Located in the upscale Shops at Wailea, Lineage stands out for its authentic food and inviting atmosphere. The menu has evolved to include Korean and Chinese flavors, featuring shareable dishes like Korean fried chicken, garlic Szechuan noodles, and wagyu kalbi short rib with roasted bone marrow.
name: Lineage
address: 3750 Wailea Alanui Dr, Wailea, HI 96753, USA

excerpt: Classic counter-service joint serving saimin, chow fun, dry noodles, manju & plate lunches.
detail_description: Sam Sato's Inc is a classic counter-service restaurant located in Wailuku, Maui. Since the 1930s, it has been a popular spot for locals and visitors alike. The restaurant is known for its affordable and hearty breakfast options, cheeseburgers, saimin, chow fun, loco moco, and plate lunches.
name: Sam Sato's Inc
address: 1750 Wili Pa Loop A, Wailuku, HI 96793, USA

detail_description: Nestled in Kula, Restaurant Marlow is a culinary treasure offering a diverse menu influenced by local ingredients and global flavors. Chef Jeff Scheer and his wife, Kaili, have crafted a dining experience that emphasizes fresh, locally grown produce to create dishes bursting with flavor. From signature pizzas to mouthwatering cioppino and vegetarian options like roasted root veg, there's something for every palate.
name: Marlow
address: 30 Kupaoa St A104, Makawao, HI 96768, USA

excerpt: Beachside eatery & sandy hub for pupu, fish tacos, tropical drinks, live music & people-watching.
detail_description: Hula Grill Kaanapali is a beachside eatery and bar that offers a relaxed atmosphere with pupu, fish tacos, tropical drinks, and live music. The restaurant features an authentic Hawaiian menu made with local ingredients and freshly caught seafood. Guests can enjoy the outdoor barefoot bar while taking in views of Molokai and Lanai beaches. The renowned Aloha Hour offers drink specials and a pupu menu with options like beef poke lettuce wraps and tandoori roasted shrimp.
name: Hula Grill Kaanapali
address: 2435 Kaanapali Pkwy, Lahaina, HI 96761, USA

excerpt: Breakfasts, fish tempura, teriyaki beef & a signature chicken katsu in a simple, casual space.
detail_description: Da Kitchen, located in Kihei and Kahului, is a popular restaurant on Maui known for its generous portions of classic Hawaiian food. Despite its suburban strip-mall location, it attracts both locals and tourists with its island soul food, including signature dishes like chicken katsu and teriyaki beef. The airport location offers a wider selection, featuring traditional plate-lunch-style fare as well as burgers and sandwiches.
name: Da Kitchen
address: 1215 S Kihei Rd suite e, Kihei, HI 96753, USA

excerpt: Family-style Hawaii Regional fare inspired by local produce, served in contemporary surrounds.
detail_description: Nestled within the luxurious Andaz Maui at Wailea, Ka'ana Kitchen offers a family-style dining experience featuring Hawaii Regional fare crafted from locally sourced ingredients. Since its opening in 2014, this award-winning restaurant has been celebrated for its innovative dishes like cinnamon roll pancakes and poached eggs with Molokai sweet potatoes. The restaurant's stunning coastal location provides breathtaking views, making it the perfect spot to savor a marvelous wine list and exceptional service.
name: Ka'ana Kitchen
address: 3550 Wailea Alanui Dr, Wailea, HI 96753, USA

excerpt: Intimate locale on the beach features Pacific Rim & Mediterranean dishes, plus a variety of wines.
detail_description: Mala Ocean Tavern is a charming beachfront restaurant that offers a blend of Pacific Rim and Mediterranean cuisine along with an extensive selection of wines. Chef Mark Ellman, a pioneer of the Hawaii Regional Cuisine movement, presents a menu featuring dishes such as ahi bruschetta, wok-fried Hawaiian fish, and vegan mushroom Bolognese pasta made with local shiitakes. The restaurant also serves signature cocktails like the Spa Day and the LBC.
name: Mala Ocean Tavern
address: 1307 Front St, Lahaina, HI 96761, USA

excerpt: Vibrant, trendy eatery featuring Japanese-Pacific Rim fare, creative sushi rolls & weekend karaoke.
detail_description: Sansei Seafood Restaurant & Sushi Bar is a trendy and vibrant eatery that offers Japanese-Pacific Rim cuisine and creative sushi rolls. Located in a plantation-style building, the restaurant is known for its contemporary atmosphere and innovative dishes. The menu features a variety of options, including panko-crusted ahi sashimi, the famous Kapalua Butterfly roll, shrimp dynamite, crab ramen, and Asian shrimp cake.
name: Sansei Seafood Restaurant & Sushi Bar
address: 600 Office Rd, Lahaina, HI 96761, USA

excerpt: Sleek Japanese venue with diverse small-plate list, sushi & specialty rolls, plus a range of drinks.
detail_description: Nuka is a sleek Japanese venue offering a diverse menu of small plates, sushi, specialty rolls, and a variety of drinks. Located in the sleepy North Shore town of Haiku, it's popular among locals for its seriously fresh sushi and izakaya-style eats. The restaurant serves unique twists on traditional rolls like the Lollipop roll and offers Asian-inspired dishes such as wasabi fries.
name: Nuka
address: 780 Haiku Rd, Haiku, HI 96708, USA

excerpt: Historic, art-filled space for elegantly plated seafood, steak & Hawaiian specialties with wine.
detail_description: Nestled in the historic town of Lahaina, Lahaina Grill has been a top dining destination for over two decades. This elegant restaurant offers a blend of locally sourced ingredients and international cooking methods to craft innovative New American cuisine. The ambiance is equally impressive, with fine china and crystal adorning the tables, vibrant paintings by renowned artist Jan Kasprzycki gracing the walls, and charming pressed tin ceilings adding to the overall inviting atmosphere.
name: Lahaina Grill
address: 127 Lahainaluna Rd, Lahaina, HI 96761, USA

excerpt: Counter-serve cafe & patio is a local go-to for breakfast deals including omelets & cinnamon rolls.
detail_description: Kihei Caffe is a popular breakfast spot located in the Kihei Kalama Village, offering a variety of delicious and filling breakfast options at reasonable prices. The menu features Hawaiian favorites like Loco Moco and Crab Cake Eggs Benedict, as well as classic dishes such as omelets and cinnamon rolls. The cafe has a cozy interior with a spacious patio for outdoor dining, making it an ideal place to enjoy freshly roasted Hawaiian coffee and hearty breakfast plates.
name: Kihei Caffe
address: 1945 S Kihei Rd, Kihei, HI 96753, USA

excerpt: Beachfront dining with sushi & other stylish Japanese creations from Iron Chef Masaharu Morimoto.
detail_description: Morimoto Maui offers beachfront dining featuring a variety of stylish Japanese creations by Iron Chef Masaharu Morimoto. The restaurant showcases a blend of Japanese and Western-inspired cuisine, highlighting the bountiful produce of Hawaii. Situated at the Andaz Maui resort, the modern architecture takes inspiration from traditional Japanese beach houses, providing an open and airy ambiance with stunning views of the beach and ocean. In addition to sushi, the menu also features dishes prepared with fresh local ingredients.
name: Morimoto Maui
address: 3550 Wailea Alanui Dr, Wailea-Makena, HI 96753, USA

excerpt: Hawaiian eatery on the Plantation Golf Course offers views from the 19th hole & elegant island fare.
detail_description: The Plantation House is a Hawaiian eatery located on the Plantation Golf Course, offering stunning views from the 19th hole and serving elegant island fare. The restaurant is renowned for its panoramic sunset vistas overlooking the lush fairways of the golf course and the neighboring islands of Molokai. Executive Chef Jojo Vasquez has curated menus for breakfast, lunch, and dinner that showcase locally sourced and inspired dishes, along with signature menu items.
name: The Plantation House
address: 2000 Plantation Club Dr, Lahaina, HI 96761, USA

excerpt: The Fairmont Kea Lani's swanky eatery has a sugarcane-plantation-era menu in a sconce-lit space.
detail_description: K Restaurant, located in the Fairmont Kea Lani, offers a unique dining experience with its sugarcane-plantation-era menu that reflects the diverse ethnic cuisine from Maui's old plantation days. The restaurant's concept is to cook up Hawaiian, Filipino, Portuguese, Korean, Puerto Rican, and European dishes in a gourmet fashion. Executive chef Jonathan Pasion has curated a menu that showcases the culinary influences of various immigrant cultures in Hawaii.
name: K Restaurant
address: 4100 Wailea Alanui Dr, Kihei, HI 96753, USA

excerpt: Open-air eatery with seasonal, locally sourced Hawaiian recipes, plus occasional live music.
detail_description: Nalu's South Shore Grill is an open-air eatery in Kihei, Maui that offers a delightful dining experience. The restaurant prides itself on serving seasonal, locally sourced Hawaiian recipes and occasionally features live music. Their breakfast menu boasts hearty comfort food like the loco moco made with local eggs and grass-fed beef, as well as the Black and Blue ahi Benedict and fluffy pineapple-banana pancakes.
name: Nalu's South Shore Grill
address: 1280 S Kihei Rd, Kihei, HI 96753, USA

detail_description: Maui Brewing Co. has made a significant impact on the craft beer scene in Maui, offering refined flavors that incorporate the island's bounty. With two locations on the Valley Isle, visitors can enjoy a chic interior, games, and live music at their Kihei tavern or savor fresh homemade food at their west side restaurant. The brewery offers four flagship beers like Bikini Blonde and Big Swell IPA, as well as limited release beers such as POG IPA and Mango Hefeweizen.
name: Maui Brewing Co.
address: 605 Lipoa Pkwy, Kihei, HI 96753, USA

excerpt: Wood-fired pizzas with organic ingredients & free-range meats, made in traditional clay ovens.
detail_description: Flatbread Company is a popular pizza joint in Paia, Vermont, known for its wood-fired pizzas made with organic ingredients and free-range meats. The restaurant has a no-reservations policy but offers 'call-ahead seating' for the waitlist. It's a family-friendly spot with a laid-back vibe and spacious outdoor patio. The menu features delicious flatbread pizzas and salads, including the Daily Specials like carne and veggie options.
name: Flatbread Company
address: 89 Hana Hwy, Paia, HI 96779, USA

excerpt: Sophisticated venue for refined, locally sourced New American cuisine in a picturesque setting.
detail_description: Nestled within the stunning Maui Tropical Plantation, The Mill House Restaurant + Bar offers a sophisticated dining experience that celebrates New American cuisine with a farm-to-table philosophy. Under the expert guidance of Executive Chef Jeff Scheer, this culinary gem crafts menus that change twice daily, showcasing the freshest local produce. Diners can indulge in an array of delightful vegetarian dishes like root vegetables paired with carrot puree or Chickpea Panisse complemented by corn puree and harissa.
name: The Mill House
address: 1670 HI-30 #1, Wailuku, HI 96793, USA

excerpt: Beachside eatery known for its seafood-driven menu, tropical drinks & family-friendly vibe.
detail_description: Leilani's on the Beach is a beachside restaurant with a focus on seafood and tropical drinks, offering a family-friendly atmosphere. Situated in the heart of Kaanapali's south beach, also known as Dig-Beach, it provides an elevated ocean view along the three-mile stretch of white sand where Hawaiian royalty used to surf and play traditional games.
name: Leilani's on the Beach
address: 2435 Kaanapali Pkwy, Lahaina, HI 96761, USA

excerpt: This upscale eatery in the Fairmont features a seafood-driven menu & lush garden setting.
detail_description: NICKS FISHMARKET is an upscale seafood restaurant located in the Fairmont Kealani Maui, offering a lush garden setting and a seafood-driven menu. The restaurant features a curved granite bar, glass wine display, and Mediterranean-inspired details that exude elegance. However, the interior decor with ocean-themed fabric upholstery and shell-shaped lighting fixtures may appear slightly outdated. One of the prominent attractions is an 800-gallon fish tank that adds to the ambiance.
name: NICKS FISHMARKET
address: 4100 Wailea Alanui Dr, Kihei, HI 96753, USA

excerpt: Renowned spot for shave ice featuring exotic flavors, such as pickled mango, lychee & passion fruit.
detail_description: Ululani's Hawaiian Shave Ice in Kihei and Lahaina is a must-visit spot for shave ice enthusiasts. They are known for their exotic flavors like pickled mango, lychee, and passion fruit. The shave ice is made with gourmet Maui-made ice cream at the bottom, extra fine shaved ice, and topped with their delicious local favorite juices and other optional toppings.
name: Ululani's Hawaiian Shave Ice - Kihei
address: 61 S Kihei Rd, Kihei, HI 96753, USA

excerpt: Pacific Rim cuisine & a popular happy hour in a casual, open-air setting on the beach.
detail_description: Sea House Restaurant, located in the Napili Kai Beach Resort, offers a casual open-air setting right on the beach. It's renowned for its Pacific Rim cuisine and popular happy hour, making it one of the best dining spots in Maui with stunning ocean views. The restaurant has won multiple awards for its breakfast and happy hour offerings.
name: Sea House Restaurant
address: 5900 Lower Honoapiilani Rd, Lahaina, HI 96761, USA

excerpt: Hyatt Regency's eatery & lounge offers Pacific Rim fare & sushi, plus views of waterfalls & sunsets.
detail_description: Nestled within the luxurious Hyatt Regency Resort, Japengo is a remarkable dining spot that offers stunning views of sunsets and waterfalls from its patio. The restaurant boasts a sophisticated and inviting ambiance with its rustic-chic facade. It is renowned for serving top-notch Asian cuisine, including exquisite sushi presentations, modern Asian dishes, and delightful desserts.
name: Japengo
address: 200 Nohea Kai Dr, Lahaina, HI 96761, USA

excerpt: Quaint trattoria with an airy patio offering modern Italian fare & an extensive wine selection.
detail_description: Matteo's Osteria is a charming trattoria known for its modern Italian cuisine and extensive wine selection. Since 2013, chef Matteo Mistura has been delighting guests with scratch-made pastas, fresh fish dishes, and an impressive wine room. The restaurant offers a globally influenced wine list featuring bottles from Italy and California to complement the local catch. With over 60 wines by the glass, it boasts one of the largest selections on Maui.
name: Matteo's Osteria
address: 161 Wailea Ike Pl A107, Wailea, HI 96753, USA

detail_description: Kitoko Maui is a unique mobile restaurant located in Kihei, offering an exceptional dining experience with its impressive dishes. The chef, formerly from the Four Seasons, showcases fine dining expertise through creations like seared swordfish bento and poke with magenta dragonfruit ponzu. The food truck is nestled in a tropical plant wonderland where guests can enjoy live music and find cozy spots among the palms to savor their meals.
name: Kitoko Maui
address: 35 Auhana Rd, Kihei, HI 96753, USA

excerpt: Relaxed seafood spot with harbor views features local seafood, prime rib & famous Hula Pie dessert.
detail_description: Kimo's Maui is a renowned seafood restaurant with stunning harbor views, offering classic Hawaiian dishes and tropical craft cocktails. The open-air dining experience provides incredible ocean vistas, making it one of the best places to eat in Lahaina. The menu features local seafood, prime rib, and their famous Hula Pie dessert. Visitors can also enjoy the signature Mai Tai cocktail made with a fresh house juice blend at the lanai bar while taking in the beauty of Maui.
name: Kimo's Maui
address: 845 Front St a, Lahaina, HI 96761, USA

excerpt: Rustic rooms in a premium property featuring a spa, plus a dramatic restaurant with mountain views.
detail_description: Nestled in the slopes of the Haleakala Crater, Kula Lodge offers rustic rooms and a spa, along with a restaurant boasting stunning mountain views. The lodge's cozy atmosphere is complemented by a botanical garden filled with vibrant proteas and flowers, providing an ideal spot for relaxation. Guests can enjoy hearty meals by the fireplace, featuring dishes like lamb chops with red wine demi-glace and Molokai sweet potato hash.
name: Kula Lodge
address: 15200 Haleakala Hwy, Kula, HI 96790, USA

excerpt: Local tradition since 1916 for cream puffs, donuts on a stick, butter rolls & other pastries.
detail_description: Komoda Store and Bakery is a beloved Maui institution that has been serving up delectable pastries since 1916. Owned by Betty and Calvin Shibuya, this charming mom-and-pop shop in Makawao is a must-visit for anyone with a sweet tooth. The bakery offers an array of traditional treats, including cream puffs, malasadas, and their famous 'stick donuts' - doughnut balls served on sticks like sweet kebabs.
name: Komoda Store and Bakery
address: 3674 Baldwin Ave, Makawao, HI 96768, USA

excerpt: Rustic-chic tavern serving Hawaiian regional cuisine, plus specialty cocktails.
detail_description: Taverna Maui is a rustic-chic tavern located in Kapalua, offering creative Italian dishes, pizzas, and specialty cocktails. The restaurant features beautiful ocean views, a wraparound bar, and an award-winning cocktail list. It's a popular spot for brunch and happy hour with its crowd-pleasing Italian menu that includes lasagna, pizza, and carbonara made with local seafood, meat, and veggies.
name: Taverna
address: 2000 Village Rd, Lahaina, HI 96761, USA

excerpt: Wolfgang Puck's glam eatery in the Four Seasons Hotel offers Californian-fusion fare & vista views.
detail_description: Spago is a glamorous eatery located in the Four Seasons Hotel, offering Californian-fusion cuisine and stunning vista views. The restaurant, opened in 2001, boasts an Asian-inspired contemporary design with unique stone, wood, and custom glass elements that frame spectacular views of the Maui coastline. Guests can indulge in a culinary experience featuring traditional Hawaiian flavors and locally sourced ingredients infused with Wolfgang Puck's California style and a touch of Asian influence.
name: Spago
address: 3900 Wailea Alanui Dr, Kihei, HI 96753, USA

excerpt: Hawaiian chain is a go-to for mahi mahi, shellfish & sushi served in a simple, casual space.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Kihei, Cafe O'Lei Kihei is a delightful dining destination that captures the essence of Hawaiian hospitality. This charming bar and restaurant boasts a vibrant atmosphere where you can savor an array of delectable dishes, from fresh seafood to sushi, all crafted with local ingredients. Whether you're indulging in their famous blackened mahi-mahi or enjoying a refreshing cocktail after a day of adventure, this casual eatery provides the perfect backdrop for relaxation.
name: Cafe O'Lei Kihei
address: 2439 S Kihei Rd #201A, Kihei, HI 96753, USA

excerpt: Convivial tavern with elevated pub eats, craft brews & cocktails, plus multiple TVs for sports fans.
detail_description: The Pint & Cork is a convivial tavern located in the Shops at Wailea, Maui. It offers elevated pub eats, craft brews, and cocktails, making it a popular spot for both residents and visitors to relax and enjoy innovative comfort food with seriously tasty craft cocktails. The tavern features multiple TVs for sports fans to catch their favorite games while sipping on local beer or refreshing cocktails. Additionally, it's an ideal location for sports watching in South Maui with easy parking available.
name: The Pint & Cork
address: 3750 Wailea Alanui Dr, Kihei, HI 96753, USA

excerpt: Cozy cafe with a scenic deck, relaxed vibe & organic coffee made from local, house-roasted beans.
detail_description: Nestled in the Keokea enclave of Kula on the serene slopes of Haleakala, Grandma's Coffee House is a beloved island institution with a rich history. Named after Minnie Franco, who traded hand-picked Maui beans in 1918, this family-operated venue offers a charming atmosphere and delectable baked goods amidst breathtaking views at its 3,000-foot elevation.
name: Grandma's Coffee House
address: 9232 Kula Hwy, Kula, HI 96790, USA

excerpt: Casual eatery for specialty sushi rolls, sashimi & other Japanese fare in a strip-mall space.
detail_description: Koiso Sushi Bar is a renowned eatery tucked away in a strip mall in Kihei, Maui. Despite its unassuming appearance, this small but acclaimed restaurant offers some of the best sushi and sashimi on the island. Chef Hiroaki tirelessly sources the freshest fish to create beautifully presented, traditionally prepared dishes that are nothing short of extraordinary. The intimate setting and personalized service provide a special dining experience that feels exclusive and welcoming.
name: Koiso Sushi Bar
address: 2395 S Kihei Rd #113, Kihei, HI 96753, USA

excerpt: Bustling spot for American eats at the Napili Shores condo complex features macadamia nut pancakes.
detail_description: The Gazebo is a popular dining spot located in the Napili Shores condo complex, offering American cuisine with a focus on breakfast. Despite its somewhat hidden location behind the resort's pool, the restaurant draws large crowds, often forming long lines even before its 7:30 am opening time. Guests waiting in line are offered fresh coffee and are rewarded with stunning ocean views and a relaxed beach-hut atmosphere upon being seated.
name: The Gazebo
address: 5315 Lower Honoapiilani Rd, Lahaina, HI 96761, USA

excerpt: Homey venue serving plant-based burritos, sandwiches & bowls, plus kombucha & funky cocktails.
detail_description: Moku Roots is a cozy eatery in Lahaina, Maui, offering a variety of plant-based burritos, sandwiches, bowls, and beverages like kombucha and creative cocktails. Founded in May 2018 by friends Alexa Caskey and Erica Gale, the restaurant was born out of Alexa's struggle to find diverse vegetarian options on the island. The menu features constantly changing dishes made with fresh organic vegetables from Mala Akala farm located just 6 miles away.
name: Moku Roots
address: 335 Keawe St #211, Lahaina, HI 96761, USA

excerpt: Casual vegan spot for wraps, sandwiches, waffles & re-interpreted global comfort foods.
detail_description: If you're on the hunt for a delightful vegan dining experience in Maui, look no further than A`A Roots. Nestled in the picturesque town of Lahaina, this charming caf is celebrated as the island's only 100% vegan spot. With a commitment to cruelty-free practices and an eco-conscious approach, A`A Roots serves up an array of wraps, sandwiches, waffles, and globally inspired comfort foods that are both delicious and nourishing.
name: A`A Roots
address: 5095 Napilihau St #103, Lahaina, HI 96761, USA

excerpt: Store with a wide variety of beers, wines, spirits & cigars, plus some artisanal foodstuffs.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Kihei, Tamura's Fine Wines & Liquors is a hidden gem that offers an impressive array of beers, wines, spirits, and cigars. This family-owned market stands out not just for its extensive liquor selection but also for its renowned poke counterarguably one of the best on the island. Locals flock here to indulge in various poke preparations that showcase fresh ingredients and authentic flavors.
name: Tamura's Fine Wines & Liquors Kihei
address: 91 E Lipoa St, Kihei, HI 96753, USA

excerpt: Murals adorn the warm interiors at this Greek-Italian eatery featuring fish caught by the owner.
detail_description: Pita Paradise is a hidden gem in the Wailea Gateway Center, offering a blend of Greek and Italian cuisine with a sea-to-table concept. The warm interiors are adorned with murals, creating a cozy atmosphere for locals and tourists alike. The restaurant prides itself on using fish caught by its owner, ensuring fresh and high-quality seafood dishes. From grilled Mahi Mahi to Mediterranean tapas and cocktails, the menu features an array of delectable options.
name: Pita Paradise
address: 34 Wailea Ike Dr, Kihei, HI 96753, USA

excerpt: Casual, BYO all-day cafe for pasta, pizza & panini, plus local dishes & breakfast staples.
detail_description: Nestled in the lush green country of Kula, 808 Bistro is a casual all-day cafe that offers a delightful mix of local dishes and breakfast staples. The restaurant's location provides easy access to various attractions such as Ho'okipa Beach for windsurfing, the artsy town of Paia, and the cowboy town of Makawao.
name: Kula Bistro
address: 4566 Lower Kula Rd, Kula, HI 96790, USA

excerpt: High-end chain serving notable chef Roy Yamaguchi's Hawaiian fusion fare in a contemporary setting.
detail_description: Roy's is a high-end chain restaurant known for serving Hawaiian fusion cuisine created by the renowned chef Roy Yamaguchi. The restaurant at the Kaanapali Golf Course offers Pacific Rim delights in a stunning mountainside setting. Signature dishes include fire-grilled Szechuan-spiced baby back ribs, blackened ahi, and hibachi-style grilled salmon. The restaurant also boasts an exceptional wine list and is famous for its iconic chocolate souffle dessert.
name: Roy's Kaanapali
address: 2290 Kaanapali Pkwy Suite A, Lahaina, HI 96761, USA

detail_description: Nestled within a Shell station in North Kihei, Havens is a delightful culinary gem that has quickly become a favorite among locals and savvy travelers alike. Founded by Maui's own Chef Zach Sato, this eatery prides itself on using fresh, locally sourced ingredients to create mouthwatering dishes. The menu features an enticing selection of temaki sushi and smash burgers, with the added bonus of noodles available at their storefront.
name: Havens
address: 30 Manao Kala St Ste 102, Kihei, HI 96753, USA
